#!/bin/sh
# dev guide — interactive getting started tutorial

DEVYSIX_CONFIG="${DEVYSIX_CONFIG:-/etc/devysix/devysix.toml}"

clear
cat <<'EOF'
  devysix guide — getting started
  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  devysix manages your system declaratively through a
  single config file: /etc/devysix/devysix.toml

  everything you want on your system lives in that file.
  devysix makes the system match it.

  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  CORE WORKFLOW

  1. edit your config
       dev edit

  2. apply it
       dev switch

  3. that's it. devysix handles packages, services,
     hostname, locale, timezone, and users.

  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  PACKAGES

  install a package and persist it to your config:
       dev apps install <package>

  remove a package and remove it from your config:
       dev apps remove <package>

  pin a package so it survives rollbacks:
       dev lock <package>

  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  GENERATIONS

  every time you run 'dev switch', a generation snapshot
  is saved. you can always go back.

  see all generations:
       dev network

  roll back to the previous generation:
       dev rollback

  roll back to a specific generation:
       dev rollback <id>

  compare two generations:
       dev diff <a> <b>

  clean up old generations:
       dev purge

  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  OTHER COMMANDS

  dev doctor          check system health
  dev update          refresh cache, show upgrades
  dev theme [name]    list or apply color themes
  dev spore <pkgs>    temporary shell with extra packages
  dev spread          export config for a fresh install
  dev services        show or validate service state
  dev active          show current generation details

  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  SERVICES

  services are declared in devysix.toml under [services].
  service definitions live in /usr/lib/devysix/services/.
  mycel-compose compiles them into s6-rc on each 'dev switch'.

  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  RHIZOMATIC DESIGN

  no central authority. every component connects directly.
  your config is the system. the system is your config.

EOF
